International Business Machines Corp Gets Selected by AXA Insurance for Integration Project in Romania-Theflyonthewall.com
Tuesday, 13 Mar 2012 08:00pm EDT
Theflyonthewall.com reported that International Business Machines Corp's smarter computing model has been selected by AXA Insurance for a four-year systems integration project in Romania designed to streamline business processes, reduce information technology costs, and uncover new business opportunities. Under the agreement signed in 2011, International Business Machines Corp will provide systems integration and management services to help streamline risk management, consolidate data to provide the company with a single view of customers, and work to lower operational costs by automating several pieces of the insurance process. Financial details were not disclosed.Â 
